<exercise id="fs-idm72467968">
<problem id="fs-idm121507488">
<para id="fs-idm185709712">How would you characterize Thomas Jefferson’s ideas on race and slavery?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm124009520">
<para id="fs-idp60915152">Although he enslaved hundreds of people in his lifetime and fathered several children with Sally Hemings, Jefferson opposed slavery. He argued that the institution should be abolished and enslaved people returned to Africa, believing that Black and White people could not live together in a free society without the result of a race war.</para>
</solution>
